FIDELITY & DEPOSIT COMPANY OF MARYLAND, a Corporation, Plaintiff in Error, v. C. A. ROBINSON, Receiver of the First National Bank of Burley, Idaho, Defendant in Error. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. August 3, 1925. No. 4482. Erank T. Wyman, of Boise, Idaho, fox’ plaintiff in error. John W. Graham, of Twin Falls, Idaho, and Oliver O. Haga, McKeen F. Morrow, and J. L. Eberlé, all of Boise, Idaho, for defendant in error.

Before GILBERT, HUNT, and RUDKIN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Affirmed on the authority of Fidelity & Deposit Company of Maryland v. C. A. Robinson, Etc., No. 4473, 7 F.(2d) 371, this day decided.
